The paper deals with combinatorial and geometric aspects of dominance drawings of directed acyclic graphs and permutations, which are topics that are typically studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of universal point sets and superpatterns, which are related to topics in computational complexity (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper includes calculations of leading constants in the bounds, which is a topic that is often studied in computational optimization (cs.CO).
